{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-20T11:26:18.425Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Core idea:"},{"type":"hardBreak"},{"type":"text","text":"Treat prompting not as “guess and hope” but as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"scientific, test-driven process"},{"type":"text","text":": you define tasks, create test cases, run prompts, observe failures, hypothesize improvements, and refine iteratively until Claude reliably succeeds."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Anthropic explicitly says:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"“Prompt engineering is a very iterative empirical science.”"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For code tasks, this becomes even more concrete:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"“We use an iterative, test-driven approach to automatically refine code generation prompts, and we analyze the outcome of this process to identify prompt improvement items that lead to test passes.”"}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What “empirical” means here"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"“Empirical” = "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"based on observation and evidence, not theory alone."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In prompt engineering for Claude:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You don’t assume a prompt is good because it sounds clear."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"measure"},{"type":"text","text":" how it performs on real test cases (including edge cases)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"observe"},{"type":"text","text":" failure patterns and use them to guide changes."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A study on prompt engineering for classification tasks recommends a systematic process:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Generate and evaluate an initial prompt."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Generate diverse baseline prompts and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"empirically select"},{"type":"text","text":" the best on a training dataset."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Experiment with different few‑shot example combinations."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Add techniques (persona, CoT, explanations) only if they improve performance on a development set."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Final evaluation on a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"held‑out test set"},{"type":"text","text":" for unbiased metrics (Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1)."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the empirical mindset: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"prompts are hypotheses; test results are data."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What “iterative” means here"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"“Iterative” = "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"improve through repeated cycles"},{"type":"text","text":", not one big rewrite."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The typical loop:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt"},{"type":"text","text":" → write an initial version."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Run"},{"type":"text","text":" → test it on a set of examples."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Observe"},{"type":"text","text":" → note where Claude fails (wrong format, hallucinations, missing reasoning, tone issues)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Hypothesize"},{"type":"text","text":" → why did it fail? What’s ambiguous? What constraint is missing?"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Refine"},{"type":"text","text":" → adjust the prompt (add examples, clarify rules, restructure, add tags)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Repeat"},{"type":"text","text":" → test again, observe, refine."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"IBM defines iterative prompting as:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"“A structured, step‑by‑step approach in prompt engineering designed to refine and optimize interactions with large language models.”"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In practice, this often looks like:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Turn 1: “Write a summary.” → Too vague."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Turn 2: Add audience and length. → Still misses key points."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Turn 3: Add structured output and examples. → Now it’s solid."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each turn is an iteration guided by what you saw before."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test-driven prompting for Claude (especially for code)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For code tasks, the empirical, iterative approach becomes "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"test-driven prompting"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Define the task + tests"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"“Define tasks → define steps → define flows.”"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Describe the function or feature you want."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ask Claude to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"write tests first"},{"type":"text","text":" (TDD style)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Run those tests to confirm they fail (because the code doesn’t exist)."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Red"},{"type":"text","text":" stage:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Define criteria (including security requirements if relevant)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ask Claude to generate only test functions."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Run tests and confirm they fail or don’t build."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Prompt to pass tests (Green)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Then:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"“Ask the AI to create the implementation specifically to pass those tests.”"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You tell Claude:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"“Write code whose only goal is to make all committed tests pass.”"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Do not modify the tests."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Run the test suite, analyze failures, adjust code, repeat until all pass."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Green"},{"type":"text","text":" stage."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Refactor while keeping tests passing (Refactor)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Finally:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"“Refine the code for cleanliness and performance while running the tests to ensure the security logic remains intact.”"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ask Claude to refactor for readability, modularity, performance."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Keep all tests passing."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Optionally use a sub‑agent to verify the implementation isn’t just overfitting to your tests."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Refactor"},{"type":"text","text":" stage."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Test‑prompt skills for Claude Code implement this explicitly:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"“The test‑prompt skill transforms prompt engineering into a disciplined, test‑driven process. By leveraging isolated subagents as ‘clean slate’ test environments, it allows developers to establish baselines (RED phase), implement minimal prompt fixes (GREEN phase), and optimize instructions (REFACTOR phase) without the bias of existing conversation history.”"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"empirical, iterative approach"},{"type":"text","text":" applied to prompts:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"RED:"},{"type":"text","text":" baseline where prompts fail."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"GREEN:"},{"type":"text","text":" minimal prompt changes that fix failures."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"REFACTOR:"},{"type":"text","text":" cleaner, more robust prompts."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How to run an empirical, iterative loop with Claude"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 1: Define the specific task"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"“The first and most crucial step is to clearly define the specific task you want Claude to perform.”"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Be explicit:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What is the input?"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What is the desired output?"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What are the constraints (length, format, no hallucinations, etc.)?"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task:\nGiven a customer email, classify it into: Billing, Bug, Feature, or Other.\nOutput: JSON with fields: { category, reason }\nConstraints:\n- Category must be exactly one of: Billing, Bug, Feature, Other.\n- Reason must be ≤ 25 words.\n- Do not guess; if unclear, set category to \"Other\" and explain why."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 2: Create diverse test cases"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"“Define the task... the next step is to create a diverse set of test cases that cover the intended use cases for your application.”"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Create 10–30 examples covering:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common cases."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Edge cases (ambiguous wording, multi-topic emails)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Negative cases (emails that look like one category but are another)."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example test set snippet:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Test 1:\nEmail: \"I was double charged this month.\"\nExpected: { category: \"Billing\", reason: \"Customer reports incorrect charging.\" }\n\nTest 2:\nEmail: \"The app crashes when I click Export to CSV.\"\nExpected: { category: \"Bug\", reason: \"Specific feature is crashing.\" }\n\nTest 3:\nEmail: \"Can you add a Google Sheets export option?\"\nExpected: { category: \"Feature\", reason: \"User requests a new capability.\" }"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 3: Craft an initial prompt"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"“Next craft an initial prompt that outlines the task definition, feed your test cases into Claude using the preliminary prompt.”"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Keep it simple but clear: role + task + output format + constraints."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 4: Run tests and observe results"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Run your prompt on all test cases and record:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Which cases pass (correct output)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Which fail, and why (wrong category, missing reason, hallucinated info, bad format)."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is your "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"empirical data"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 5: Diagnose and hypothesize improvements"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For each failure, ask:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What was ambiguous in the prompt?"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Did Claude misunderstand the category boundaries?"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Did it ignore the format constraint?"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Was it missing an example for this pattern?"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Then hypothesize:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"“Add one more example for ambiguous ‘Export’ queries.”"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"“Clarify that ‘Export’ bugs are Bugs, not Features.”"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"“Emphasize that category must be exactly one of the four values.”"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 6: Refine the prompt and retest"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Adjust the prompt:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Add clarifying text."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Add few‑shot examples."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use XML tags like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<examples>"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<rules>"},{"type":"text","text":" to structure the prompt."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Then "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"retest"},{"type":"text","text":" on the same set."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the loop from IBM:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"“Iterative prompting is a structured, step‑by‑step approach designed to refine and optimize interactions with LLMs.”"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Repeat until performance is stable and high."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why this works especially well with Claude"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude’s best practices page emphasizes:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Clarity and directness."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Few‑shot examples."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"XML structuring."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Thinking steps and self‑critique."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompt chaining."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All of these are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"highly amenable to empirical, iterative refinement"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You can test different phrasings of constraints and see which reduces errors."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You can try different example sets and measure F1 improvement."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You can test whether adding "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<thinking>"},{"type":"text","text":" blocks improves correctness on complex tasks."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A research paper on code generation prompts confirms:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"“We use an iterative, test-driven approach to automatically refine code generation prompts, and we analyze the outcome of this process to identify prompt improvement items that lead to test passes.”"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is exactly how you should treat Claude prompts: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"as hypotheses validated by tests."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Practical checklist for an empirical, iterative prompt workflow"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this as a mental checklist:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Define the task clearly."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Input, output, constraints, edge cases."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Create a test set."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common + edge + negative cases."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Label expected outputs."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Write an initial prompt."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Role, task, format, constraints, maybe 1–2 examples."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Run tests and record results."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Accuracy, wrong format, hallucinations, missing reasoning."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Diagnose failures."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What’s ambiguous? What’s missing?"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Hypothesize improvements."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Add examples, clarify rules, restructure with tags."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Refine and retest."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Repeat until stable."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Finalize on a held‑out test set."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Confirm performance on unseen data."}]}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"empirical, iterative approach"},{"type":"text","text":" in action: treat prompts as evolving artifacts, improved by evidence, not by intuition alone."}]}]}}
